In Spring Boot application, Servlet, and listener are registered either as a Spring @Bean or 
by scanning the @WebServlet and @WebListener annotated classes with an embedded container.

You can use the ServletRegistrationBean and ServletListenerRegistrationBean classes to register the Servlet
and listener respectively.

This Project shows you how to use the Servlet and listener in Spring Boot application by registering them as a @Bean.

you can use URL http://localhost:8080/appServlet?name=Sathish%20Kariyanna